Package com.vector.cfg.gen.core.bswmdmodel.exceptions

Exceptions thrown by access methods of the generated BswmdModel.

See: Description

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    BswmdModelAttributeNotExistsException
    Thrown to indicate that a requested attribute of a model object does not exist.
    BswmdModelException
    Thrown to indicate that a bswmd model access has failed.
    BswmdModelInvalidRequestException
    The BswmdModelInvalidRequestException represents any invalid request issued by an untyped access to the BswmdModel.
    BswmdModelNotExistsException
    Thrown to indicate that a requested model object does not exist.
    BswmdModelParameterHasIllegalValueException
    Thrown to indicate that the model object has an illegal value for the parameter type.
    BswmdModelParameterHasNoValueException
    Thrown to indicate that the model object has no value.
    BswmdModelReferenceTargetException
    Thrown to indicate that the model object has an illegal reference target.
    BswmdModelWrongQuantityException
    Thrown to indicate that a requested model object does not exist.

Package com.vector.cfg.gen.core.bswmdmodel.exceptions Description

Exceptions thrown by access methods of the generated BswmdModel.
